Nigeria’s Anti-Corruption Body Recovers $6.5 Billion, Punch Says

-- B y   P a u l   O k o l o
-- 
2011-02-24T09:18:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/nigeria-s-anti-corruption-body-recovers-6-5-billion-punch-says.html
Nigeria’s Economic and Financial
Crimes Commission recovered $6.5 billion in its fight against
corruption in the past two years, the  Punch  reported, citing the
head of the agency, Farida Waziri.  The  agency  won court judgments in 150 cases and is
prosecuting 1,500 more against suspects, the Lagos-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Okolo in Abuja 
 pokolo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 